After that, he dropped 5 cookies, so he had 2x + 15 - 5 = 2x + 10 cookies left.
We know that the total number of cookies is 110, so we can set up the equation 2x + 10 = 110.
Solving this equation, we subtract 10 from both sides to get 2x = 100.
Finally, we divide both sides by 2 to find x, which represents the number of cookies Henry baked last year. 
x = 100 / 2 = 50.
Therefore, Henry baked 50 cookies last year.
The answer is 50.
